WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.041
This is the team, on one page.

p02
00:00:02.606 --> 00:00:07.013
The Employees screen is where you go when the question is about a person, not a wash.

p03
00:00:07.353 --> 00:00:10.437
Headcount up top, a few charts, then the directory.

p04
00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:12.424
Start with the four tiles.

p05
00:00:12.710 --> 00:00:14.794
They give you the whole crew at a glance.

p06
00:00:15.110 --> 00:00:19.670
Everyone on the books, who's active, and the full-time against part-time split,

p07
00:00:19.959 --> 00:00:23.934
so a staffing question gets answered before you ever scroll to the table.

p08
00:00:24.456 --> 00:00:25.376
Now the charts.

p09
00:00:25.924 --> 00:00:28.453
The first tracks headcount over the last year, and right now it's trending up.

p10
00:00:28.707 --> 00:00:30.450
When someone asks whether the team is growing, this is your answer in one line,

p11
00:00:30.965 --> 00:00:37.529
and you skip pulling a report to get it.

p12
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.393
The middle chart splits your people by site.

p13
00:00:40.957 --> 00:00:44.066
It's the fast read on where everyone actually sits,

p14
00:00:44.313 --> 00:00:49.497
which is exactly what you want when one location calls in short a body on a Saturday morning.

p15
00:00:49.988 --> 00:00:50.594
Third chart, same crew, different cut.

p16
00:00:50.914 --> 00:00:52.669
Full-time against part-time as a percentage, plus the count of anyone inactive.

p17
00:00:53.245 --> 00:01:01.626
It says the same thing as the tiles, drawn for the eye.

p18
00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:03.458
Down to the directory.

p19
00:01:03.929 --> 00:01:05.875
Notice the two buttons in its corner.

p20
00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:09.078
One exports data, one starts a new hire.

p21
00:01:09.385 --> 00:01:12.854
We're only reading today, so find them and leave them where they are.

p22
00:01:13.412 --> 00:01:14.692
Read the column headers.

p23
00:01:15.039 --> 00:01:15.485
Name, phone, hire date, type, status, location.

p24
00:01:15.827 --> 00:01:16.225
Six columns, and the name cell doubles as a badge:

p25
00:01:16.517 --> 00:01:17.230
an avatar and the person's role sit right next to who they are,

p26
00:01:17.531 --> 00:01:29.360
so the job is obvious before you open a thing.

p27
00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:31.496
Look at one row.

p28
00:01:31.496 --> 00:01:34.700
A shift manager, full-time, active, at one of the sites.

p29
00:01:34.700 --> 00:01:37.532
Run your eye down the role chips

p30
00:01:37.532 --> 00:01:41.377
and you've read half the team's jobs without opening a single record.

p31
00:01:41.927 --> 00:01:44.324
On a real site the roster runs long.

p32
00:01:44.628 --> 00:01:46.684
That's what the search box and filters are for:

p33
00:01:46.992 --> 00:01:49.848
type a name, narrow the list, jump to your person.

p34
00:01:50.311 --> 00:01:54.132
Here it's a five-row sample, so everyone already fits on one page.

p35
00:01:54.646 --> 00:01:56.198
Click a name to open the record.

p36
00:01:56.553 --> 00:01:58.797
One click, and the list becomes a person.

p37
00:01:59.256 --> 00:02:03.206
The header introduces him with a role chip, his site, and his employment type.

p38
00:02:03.718 --> 00:02:07.173
Three buttons sit beside it, and Back is the only one we touch.

p39
00:02:07.664 --> 00:02:10.178
Below, five tiles size him up fast:

p40
00:02:10.439 --> 00:02:13.377
three years in, a hundred sixty eight hours this month,

p41
00:02:13.585 --> 00:02:18.000
attendance above ninety seven percent, and a performance score of four point six.

p42
00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:20.030
Look across the top of the file.

p43
00:02:20.321 --> 00:02:21.330
Seven tabs: overview, personal info, employment, schedule,

p44
00:02:21.739 --> 00:02:23.586
emergency contact, notes and audit, and training.

p45
00:02:23.874 --> 00:02:24.588
That's the whole person, sorted into seven drawers, and you land in the first one.

p46
00:02:24.938 --> 00:02:39.912
Worth knowing this layout is the live one, not the old WashAssist record.

p47
00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:41.758
Stay on Overview.

p48
00:02:42.155 --> 00:02:45.456
This is the dashboard for one person, five panels deep.

p49
00:02:46.096 --> 00:02:47.634
Hours worked, month by month.

p50
00:02:47.937 --> 00:02:51.565
How those hours split between regular time, overtime, and leave.

p51
00:02:52.425 --> 00:02:56.015
Attendance across the year, with every missed shift counted.

p52
00:02:56.699 --> 00:02:59.823
Earnings, closing in on fifteen thousand for the year.

p53
00:03:00.327 --> 00:03:03.523
And a review trend running well above the location average.

p54
00:03:04.168 --> 00:03:08.000
When a manager asks how someone is doing, this one tab answers it.

p55
00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:10.828
Six more tabs sit beside Overview.

p56
00:03:11.321 --> 00:03:12.516
Each one is a drawer.

p57
00:03:13.316 --> 00:03:17.066
Personal info holds identity and address, with the social masked.

p58
00:03:17.653 --> 00:03:21.384
Employment carries role, pay, reporting line, and benefits.

p59
00:03:21.927 --> 00:03:25.125
Schedule pairs the current week with recent time clock punches.

p60
00:03:25.604 --> 00:03:28.118
Emergency contact adds the medical basics.

p61
00:03:28.594 --> 00:03:32.223
Notes and audit keeps a dated trail of every change to the record.

p62
00:03:32.761 --> 00:03:36.946
And training tracks Academy courses, with an assign button we leave alone.

p63
00:03:37.360 --> 00:03:39.534
One rule holds this whole lesson.

p64
00:03:40.324 --> 00:03:43.693
We opened the record, read it, and changed nothing in it.

p65
00:03:44.566 --> 00:03:49.594
Editing a person is a real workflow with its own approvals, and this lesson stays clear of it.

p66
00:03:50.072 --> 00:03:50.909
So click Back.

p67
00:03:52.086 --> 00:03:55.325
The list returns, and the record sits exactly as you found it.

p68
00:03:55.760 --> 00:03:57.603
So that's the Employees page.

p69
00:03:58.091 --> 00:03:59.292
A directory up front: headcount, a few charts, and a table you can search.

p70
00:03:59.816 --> 00:04:02.769
Behind any name, a seven-tab file with Overview as its home.

p71
00:04:03.214 --> 00:04:07.271
When a shift question walks in, start here

p72
00:04:07.995 --> 00:04:13.211
and let the rest of the Team module branch off from it.

